caption: This set of golden statues is found in the Bosquet de l'Arc de Triomphe. At the entrance to the grove there are a number of white marble statues with figures from Greek and Roman mythology.

The large gilded group of figures is located in the Bosquet de l'Arc de Triomphe, east of the Allée d'Eau. It was decorated in 1676 with decor alluding to military victories. Among other things, a triumphal arch was erected there, which gave the grove its name.
